ill a mob in 30-60 seconds.<P>Second is the fact that in most groups only one toon is taking any dmg.  The primary tank.  You can however stack both pact and sb for 800 hps of healing.  You will need to use either Vexxing or a deflux after the BoD wears off to maintain hps tho.<P>Third problem is, the only way to be able to do this much healing, like he claims, is to Pact one person, SB the next, Pact, SB etc.  Well the only time thats required is when something is using AE attacks.  When is the only time you get attacked by AEs?  Thats right raids.  What can you not use on ubermobs that are the target of raids?  That right, lifetaps or Bod type spells.<P>That said .. a necro can supplement a clerics healing enought that, yes, you can pull nonstop in a regular exp group.  Give it a try and see, but dont be too jealous guys.  Clerics are still by far the most efficient healers in the game.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
